==English==
===Etymology===
From English ''controller'' blended with French ''compte'' ("account")

===Pronunciation===
[kənˈtrəʊlə], [kənˈtroʊləɹ]
:(The ''p'' is silent, thus ''comptroller'' is a homophone of ''controller'')

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''comptroller'''
#the [[chief]] [[accountant]] of a [[company]] or [[government]]


====Synonyms====
: [[administrator]] – n. 
: [[foreman]] – n. 
: [[chief]], [[head]] – n., [[head man]]
: [[controller]] OR [[comptroller]] – n. 
: [[overseer]] – n. 
: [[organizer]] – n. 
: [[superintendent]] – n. 
: [[supervisor]] – n. 


